<br>
He's playing the UN showing that it truly is a worthless world government incapable of dealing with anything except minor regional conflicts.  I find it simply amazing that a council of governments, elected by no one mind you and in turn not accountable to the electorate, with a myriad of interests that they are beholden to, can usurp the sovereignty of a country by giving a handful of socialist countries absolute veto power.  Why should a country scede their sovereignty to the UN? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=everas>Everas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>AD's Iksar Monk_0354</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#333333>(3/2/03 1:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissenters</span><hr size=1> Either that or Bush's administration is playing the American public and proving what a bunch of ignorant, mindless, sycophants we really are.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=counsel4u>Counsel4u</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(3/2/03 5:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Friends in Iraq</span><hr size=1> My heart goes out to the people of Iraq.<br>
<br>
I think it's sad the world debates something so bitterly when overwhelming majorities of the people in Iraq are waiting for this to happen.  I for one will be honored to fight for my brothers and sisters in Iraq who want freedom.<br>
<br>
Iraq has the potential to be a great nation.  They have more natural resources then most European countries.  The wealth the people could enjoy is hindered by one thing alone... the tyranny under which they live.<br>
<br>
So you can spin your oil argument (which is dumb because we will spend more money fighting and giving aide then we could ever get out of Iraq), you can spin your UN argument, you can spin your &quot;America thinks it's so awesome blah blah&quot; argument, you can spin your &quot;but what about Korea&quot; argument... but until you come up with a better plan to really help the people in Iraq, you just look like someone who is focused on your own importance in the world, and not the well-being of the people which inhabit it.<br>
<br>
Who cares how the people get liberated, so long as they are free?  I think it would only be a jealous and bitter people.  I think its sad the world demands a self-interest of a nation before it lends a hand to its neighbor.  I think that time has ended though for the US.<br>
<br>
And those who wish to join us in a coalition will be those who care about the people of the world, and hope that everyone can breathe free air and enjoy things like internet forums and free speech.  But there are so many who dont, and that wont change without action from those who are strong enough to do something about it.<br>
<br>
That should be the burden of freedom... to spread it through the world as fast as possible... not to fight over who does the spreading or to make a big bureaucratic mess to figure that out.  If you don't feel that way, then you really don't know what you have...<br>
